    • getPlaceToCompare

      public static ServiceProviderPlace getPlaceToCompare(Configurator configG) throws ClassNotFoundException, InstantiationException, IllegalAccessException, InvocationTargetException, NoSuchMethodException, SecurityException
      Given a config which contains a 'PLACE_TO_COMPARE' directive, instantiate the referenced place with its usual configuration
      Parameters:
      configG - from an existing place which is scanned for PLACE_TO_COMPARE, which should reference a place that the developer wants to compare against
      Returns:
      the instantiated place if configured
      Throws:
      ClassNotFoundException - if we can't find the other place
      SecurityException - if we can't access the String constructor for the other place
      NoSuchMethodException - if there isn't an accessible constructor for the other place
      InvocationTargetException - if the underlying constructor throws an exception
      IllegalAccessException - if the Constructor object is enforcing Java language access control and the underlying constructor is inaccessible.
      InstantiationException - if the class that declares the underlying constructor represents an abstract class.

    • compareToPlace

      public static String compareToPlace(List<IBaseDataObject> newResults, IBaseDataObject ibdoForNewPlace, ServiceProviderPlace newPlace, String newMethodName, ServiceProviderPlace oldPlace, String oldMethodName, DiffCheckConfiguration options) throws NoSuchMethodException, SecurityException, IllegalAccessException, IllegalArgumentException, InvocationTargetException
      Used to compare a 'new' place with another, usually during development aimed at replacing the 'old' place.
      Parameters:
      newResults - an empty list to add results into from running the newPlace
      ibdoForNewPlace - the actual BDO being passed in for comparison
      newPlace - the new place we're comparing 'from'
      newMethodName - to use when comparing (e.g. processHeavyDuty)
      oldPlace - to compare against
      oldMethodName - to use when comparing (e.g. processHeavyDuty)
      options - DiffCheckConfiguration to configure diffing options
      Returns:
      a readable string of differences to log or use elsewhere.
      Throws:
      SecurityException - if we can't access the String constructor for the other place
      NoSuchMethodException - if there isn't an accessible constructor for the other place
      InvocationTargetException - if the underlying constructor throws an exception
      IllegalArgumentException - if the number of actual and formal parameters differ; if an unwrapping conversion for primitive arguments fails; or if, after possible unwrapping, a parameter value cannot be converted to the corresponding formal parameter type by a method invocation conversion; if this constructor pertains to an enum class
      IllegalAccessException - if the Constructor object is enforcing Java language access control and the underlying constructor is inaccessible.

    • checkDifferences

      public static String checkDifferences(IBaseDataObject ibdoForOldPlace, IBaseDataObject ibdoForNewPlace, List<IBaseDataObject> oldResults, List<IBaseDataObject> newResults, String identifier, DiffCheckConfiguration options)
      Given two BDOs and results from two processing place runs, compare them and log any differences.
      Parameters:
      ibdoForOldPlace - likely a cloned object of the 'new' place object
      ibdoForNewPlace - the 'main' BDO that was originally passed in from upstream
      oldResults - from the 'old' run with the 'ibdoForOldPlace' object
      newResults - from the 'new' run with the 'ibdoForNewPlace' object
      identifier - to highlight any differences in logs
      options - DiffCheckConfiguration to configure diffing options
      Returns:
      the string of differences, or null if there aren't any
